The Effect of altering ADL thresholds on active life expectancy estimates for 
older persons.

Lynch SM(1), Brown JS, Harmsen KG.

Author information:
(1)Department of Sociology and Office of Population Research, Princeton 
University, Princeton, New Jersey 08544, USA. slynch@princeton.edu

OBJECTIVES: Research on disability and active life expectancy (ALE) has often 
criticized the measurement of disability but has rarely empirically investigated 
the effect of changing measurement. The purpose of this study was to determine 
whether altering the number of activities of daily living (ADLs) required to 
consider an individual "disabled" affects population-based ALE estimates after 
considering parametric uncertainty and sampling error.
METHODS: The authors develop a Bayesian approach to estimating multistate life 
